# For a limited range, protein concentration can be estimated from absorbance (595 nm) with a linear regression. Alternatively, protein concentration can be estimated with a quadratic regression. Both estimates are performed and compared here.
##### first: LINEAR regression #####
#linear model for all data
linear_model_whole <- lm(protein_concentration_mg_per_mL ~ absorbance_corrected, data = dat)

#linear model should only be from absorbance range 0.2 to 1.0 (non-linear outside of this range)
linear_model <- lm(protein_concentration_mg_per_mL ~ absorbance_corrected, data = subset(dat, protein_concentration_mg_per_mL >= 0.2 & protein_concentration_mg_per_mL <= 1.0))
## [1] "Model: y =  2.1 *x + -0.026"

##### second: quadratic regression #####
quad_model <- lm(protein_concentration_mg_per_mL ~ absorbance_corrected + I(absorbance_corrected^2), data = dat)
## [1] "Model: y =  3.985 *x^2 + 0.417 *x + 0.082"
